display.resource: The metric definition of App Service Plan
display.operation: Read App Service Plan metric definitions
display.description: Gets the available metrics for App Service Plan

metricSpecifications.name: CpuPercentage
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The average CPU used across all instances of the plan.

metricSpecifications.name: MemoryPercentage
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The average memory used across all instances of the plan.

metricSpecifications.name: DiskQueueLength
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The average number of both read and write requests that were queued on storage. A high disk queue length is an indication of an app that might be slowing down because of excessive disk I/O.

metricSpecifications.name: HttpQueueLength
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The average number of HTTP requests that had to sit on the queue before being fulfilled. A high or increasing HTTP Queue length is a symptom of a plan under heavy load.

metricSpecifications.name: BytesReceived
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The average incoming bandwidth used across all instances of the plan.

metricSpecifications.name: BytesSent
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The average outgoing bandwidth used across all instances of the plan.

metricSpecifications.name: TcpSynSent
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The average number of sockets in SYN_SENT state across all the instances of the plan.

metricSpecifications.name: TcpSynReceived
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The average number of sockets in SYN_RCVD state across all the instances of the plan.

metricSpecifications.name: TcpEstablished
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The average number of sockets in ESTABLISHED state across all the instances of the plan.

metricSpecifications.name: TcpFinWait1
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The average number of sockets in FIN_WAIT_1 state across all the instances of the plan.

metricSpecifications.name: TcpFinWait2
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The average number of sockets in FIN_WAIT_2 state across all the instances of the plan.

metricSpecifications.name: TcpClosing
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The average number of sockets in CLOSING state across all the instances of the plan.

metricSpecifications.name: TcpCloseWait
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The average number of sockets in CLOSE_WAIT state across all the instances of the plan.

metricSpecifications.name: TcpLastAck
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The average number of sockets in LAST_ACK state across all the instances of the plan.

metricSpecifications.name: TcpTimeWait
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The average number of sockets in TIME_WAIT state across all the instances of the plan.

metricSpecifications.name: SocketInboundAll
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The average number of sockets used for incoming HTTP requests across all the instances of the plan.

metricSpecifications.name: SocketOutboundAll
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The average number of sockets used for outbound connections across all the instances of the plan irrespective of their TCP states. Having too many outbound connections can cause connectivity errors.

metricSpecifications.name: SocketOutboundEstablished
metricSpecifications.displayName: Established Socket Count for Outbound Requests
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The average number of sockets in ESTABLISHED state used for outbound connections across all the instances of the plan.

metricSpecifications.name: SocketOutboundTimeWait
metricSpecifications.displayName: Time Wait Socket Count for Outbound Requests
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The average number of sockets in TIME_WAIT state used for outbound connections across all the instances of the plan. High or increasing outbound socket counts in TIME_WAIT state can cause connectivity errors.

metricSpecifications.name: SocketLoopback
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The average number of sockets used for loopback connections across all the instances of the plan.

display.resource: The metric definition of Web App
display.description: Gets the available metrics for Web App

metricSpecifications.name: CpuTime
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The amount of CPU consumed by the app, in seconds. For more information about this metric. Please see https://aka.ms/website-monitor-cpu-time-vs-cpu-percentage (CPU time vs CPU percentage).

metricSpecifications.name: ScmCpuTime
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: ScmCpuTime

metricSpecifications.name: Requests
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The total number of requests regardless of their resulting HTTP status code.

metricSpecifications.name: BytesReceived
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The amount of incoming bandwidth consumed by the app, in MiB.

metricSpecifications.name: BytesSent
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The amount of outgoing bandwidth consumed by the app, in MiB.

metricSpecifications.name: Http101
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The count of requests resulting in an HTTP status code 101.

metricSpecifications.name: Http2xx
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The count of requests resulting in an HTTP status code ≥ 200 but < 300.

metricSpecifications.name: Http3xx
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The count of requests resulting in an HTTP status code ≥ 300 but < 400.

metricSpecifications.name: Http401
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The count of requests resulting in HTTP 401 status code.

metricSpecifications.name: Http403
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The count of requests resulting in HTTP 403 status code.

metricSpecifications.name: Http404
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The count of requests resulting in HTTP 404 status code.

metricSpecifications.name: Http406
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The count of requests resulting in HTTP 406 status code.

metricSpecifications.name: Http4xx
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The count of requests resulting in an HTTP status code ≥ 400 but < 500.

metricSpecifications.name: Http5xx
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The count of requests resulting in an HTTP status code ≥ 500 but < 600.

metricSpecifications.name: MemoryWorkingSet
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The current amount of memory used by the app, in MiB.

metricSpecifications.name: AverageMemoryWorkingSet
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The average amount of memory used by the app, in megabytes (MiB).

metricSpecifications.name: AverageResponseTime
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The average time taken for the app to serve requests, in seconds.

metricSpecifications.name: HttpResponseTime
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The time taken for the app to serve requests, in seconds.

metricSpecifications.name: FunctionExecutionUnits
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: Function Execution Units

metricSpecifications.name: FunctionExecutionCount
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: Function Execution Count

metricSpecifications.name: AppConnections
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The number of bound sockets existing in the sandbox (w3wp.exe and its child processes). A bound socket is created by calling bind()/connect() APIs and remains until said socket is closed with CloseHandle()/closesocket().

metricSpecifications.name: Handles
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The total number of handles currently open by the app process.

metricSpecifications.name: Threads
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The number of threads currently active in the app process.

metricSpecifications.name: PrivateBytes
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: Private Bytes is the current size, in bytes, of memory that the app process has allocated that can't be shared with other processes.

metricSpecifications.name: ScmPrivateBytes
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: ScmPrivateBytes

metricSpecifications.name: IoReadBytesPerSecond
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The rate at which the app process is reading bytes from I/O operations.

metricSpecifications.name: IoWriteBytesPerSecond
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The rate at which the app process is writing bytes to I/O operations.

metricSpecifications.name: IoOtherBytesPerSecond
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The rate at which the app process is issuing bytes to I/O operations that don't involve data, such as control operations.

metricSpecifications.name: IoReadOperationsPerSecond
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The rate at which the app process is issuing read I/O operations.

metricSpecifications.name: IoWriteOperationsPerSecond
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The rate at which the app process is issuing write I/O operations.

metricSpecifications.name: IoOtherOperationsPerSecond
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The rate at which the app process is issuing I/O operations that aren't read or write operations.

metricSpecifications.name: RequestsInApplicationQueue
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The number of requests in the application request queue.

metricSpecifications.name: CurrentAssemblies
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The current number of Assemblies loaded across all AppDomains in this application.

metricSpecifications.name: TotalAppDomains
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The current number of AppDomains loaded in this application.

metricSpecifications.name: TotalAppDomainsUnloaded
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The total number of AppDomains unloaded since the start of the application.

metricSpecifications.name: Gen0Collections
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The number of times the generation 0 objects are garbage collected since the start of the app process. Higher generation GCs include all lower generation GCs.

metricSpecifications.name: Gen1Collections
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The number of times the generation 1 objects are garbage collected since the start of the app process. Higher generation GCs include all lower generation GCs.

metricSpecifications.name: Gen2Collections
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: The number of times the generation 2 objects are garbage collected since the start of the app process.

metricSpecifications.name: HealthCheckStatus
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: Health check status

metricSpecifications.name: FileSystemUsage
metricSpecifications.displayDescription: Percentage of filesystem quota consumed by the app.
